---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '9 April 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Cookie Policy | FisherDigital"
  description="What cookies the FisherDigital website uses, why we use them, and how to manage your cookie preferences."
  schemaType="legal"
>
  <section class="section-light py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">

      <!-- Header -->
      <p class="label mb-4">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-4">
        Cookie Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mb-12">
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-base leading-relaxed">

        <!-- Intro -->
        <div>
          <p>
            This policy explains what cookies our website uses and why. We have kept it short
            because cookies really are not that complicated.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- What are cookies -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">What are cookies?</h2>
          <p>
            Cookies are small text files that websites store on your device. They help sites
            remember things about your visit, like your preferences or how you got there.
            They are used by almost every website on the internet.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Essential cookies -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Essential cookies</h2>
          <p>
            These cookies are needed for the site to work properly. They handle basic things
            like page navigation and security. Without them, the site would not function.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-sm border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-base-darker">
                  <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-500 text-text border-b border-border">Cookie</th>
                  <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-500 text-text border-b border-border">Purpose</th>
                  <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-500 text-text border-b border-border">Duration</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="text-text-secondary">
                <tr class="border-b border-border">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">cookie_consent</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Remembers your cookie preferences so we do not ask you again every visit.</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">1 year</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-text-muted">
            Essential cookies cannot be turned off because the site needs them to function.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Analytics cookies -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Analytics cookies</h2>
          <p>
            We use Google Analytics to understand how people use our site. This helps us figure
            out which pages are useful, where visitors come from, and what we can improve. The
            data is anonymised, so we cannot identify you personally from it.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-sm border border-border rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
              <thead>
                <tr class="bg-base-darker">
                  <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-500 text-text border-b border-border">Cookie</th>
                  <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-500 text-text border-b border-border">Purpose</th>
                  <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-500 text-text border-b border-border">Duration</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="text-text-secondary">
                <tr class="border-b border-border">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">_ga</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Distinguishes unique visitors to the site.</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">2 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-border">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">_ga_*</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Used by Google Analytics to maintain session state.</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">2 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs">_gid</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Distinguishes unique visitors within a 24-hour window.</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">24 hours</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- How to manage -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">How to manage cookies</h2>
          <p>
            You can control cookies through your browser settings. Every browser is slightly different,
            but you can usually find cookie settings under "Privacy" or "Security". Here are links
            to cookie management instructions for the most common browsers:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-3 text-text-secondary">
            <li>
              <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline">Google Chrome</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enhanced-tracking-protection-firefox-desktop" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline">Mozilla Firefox</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-gb/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline">Safari</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/manage-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-view-allow-block-delete-and-use-168dab11-0753-043d-7c16-ede5947fc64d" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline">Microsoft Edge</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4">
            You can also opt out of Google Analytics specifically by installing the
            <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent hover:underline">Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on</a>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Blocking cookies may affect how some parts of our site work, but the core content
            will still be fully accessible.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- No marketing or tracking cookies -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">What we do not use</h2>
          <p>
            We do not use advertising cookies, social media tracking pixels, or any kind of
            cross-site tracking. We are not interested in following you around the internet.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Changes -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Changes to this policy</h2>
          <p>
            If we start using new cookies, we will update this page and the "last updated" date
            at the top. If the change is significant, we will let you know through a banner on
            the site.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <div class="pt-6 border-t border-border">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl font-600 tracking-tight text-text mb-3">Questions?</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions about cookies on our site, get in touch:
          </p>
          <div class="mt-4 text-text-secondary">
            <p>FisherDigital</p>
            <p>Bristol, United Kingdom</p>
            <p>
              <a href="mailto:fisherwebco@gmail.com" class="text-accent hover:underline">fisherwebco@gmail.com</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
